Exampe: function as a returned value

rexp: generate values from an Exponential distribution \(f(x;\lambda)=\begin{cases} \lambda e^{-\lambda x} & x\ge 0 \\ 0 & x&lt;0. \end{cases}\).
notice that a function is returned


x = rexp(100, rate = 4)

llExp = function(DATA) { #log-likelyhood
   n = length(DATA)
   sumx = sum(DATA)
   return(function(mu) {n * log(mu) - mu * sumx})
}

myLL = llExp(x)
myLL

function (mu) 
{
    n * log(mu) - mu * sumx
}
